===Etymology 1===
Often thought to be related to {{och-l|泣|to weep|tr=*k-r̥əp}} ({{zh-ref|Mei, 1980b}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}).

However, {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007, 2015)}} finds this phonologically problematic. He instead proposes that {{och-l|淚|tr=*r(i)uts}} derives from {{och-l|流|tr=*r(i)u|to flow}} + {{m|und|*-t|pos=suffix in nouns for naturally occurring things}}, literally "the things that are flowing".

